nodes.documentation:
@notice Provides an interface for gas-efficient operations on four uint64 type
         variables tightly packed into one uint256 variable stored in memory
nodes.name: Packed64x4

nodes.documentation: @dev Returns uint64 variable stored on position `n` as uint256
nodes.name: get

nodes.documentation:
@dev Writes value stored in passed `x` variable on position `n`.
      The passed value must be less or equal to UINT64_MAX.
      If the passed value exceeds UINT64_MAX method will
      revert with a "PACKED_OVERFLOW" error message
nodes.name: set

nodes.documentation:
@dev Adds value stored in passed `x` variable to variable stored on position `n`
      using SafeMath lib
nodes.name: add

nodes.documentation:
@dev Subtract value stored in passed `x` variable from variable stored on position `n`
      using SafeMath lib
nodes.name: sub

nodes.documentation:
@title SafeMath
@dev Math operations with safety checks that revert on error
nodes.name: SafeMath

nodes.documentation: @dev Multiplies two numbers, reverts on overflow.
nodes.name: mul

nodes.documentation: @dev Integer division of two numbers truncating the quotient, reverts on division by zero.
nodes.name: div

nodes.documentation: @dev Subtracts two numbers, reverts on overflow (i.e. if subtrahend is greater than minuend).
nodes.name: sub

nodes.documentation: @dev Adds two numbers, reverts on overflow.
nodes.name: add

nodes.documentation:
@dev Divides two numbers and returns the remainder (unsigned integer modulo),
reverts when dividing by zero.
nodes.name: mod
